HEADWORD: Bignoniaceous
<hw>Big*no`ni*a"ceous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Of pertaining to, or resembling, the family of
plants of which the <stype>trumpet flower</stype> (also called
<stype>trumpet creeper</stype> and <stype>trumpet vine</stype>) is an
example.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

